.TH CODEX_PLUGIN_MARKETPLACE_UPGRADE 1 "July 2026" "codex-cli 0.142.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
codex\-plugin\-marketplace\-upgrade \- Refresh configured Git marketplace snapshots.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.EX
Usage: codex plugin marketplace upgrade [OPTIONS] [MARKETPLACE_NAME]

.EE
.SH DESCRIPTION
Refresh configured Git marketplace snapshots.
.PP
Omit MARKETPLACE_NAME to upgrade all configured Git marketplaces.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B [MARKETPLACE_NAME]
Optional configured marketplace name to upgrade. Omit to upgrade all Git marketplaces
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-config <key=value>
Override a configuration value that would otherwise be loaded from `~/.codex/config.toml`. Use a dotted path (`foo.bar.baz`) to override nested values. The `value` portion is parsed as TOML. If it fails to parse as TOML, the raw string is used as a literal.
.PP
Examples: \- `\-c model="o3"` \- `\-c 'sandbox_permissions=["disk\-full\-read\-access"]'` \- `\-c shell_environment_policy.inherit=all`
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output upgrade result as JSON
.TP
.B \-\-enable <FEATURE>
Enable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=true`
.TP
.B \-\-disable <FEATURE>
Disable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=false`
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help (see a summary with '\-h')
Examples:
.TP
.B codex plugin marketplace upgrade
.TP
.B codex plugin marketplace upgrade debug
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR codex (1),
.BR codex\-plugin\-marketplace (1)
